    "summary": "Honeycomb exposes a region-specific REST API with an OpenAPI spec and a streamable-HTTP MCP server; both require Honeycomb-issued credentials, with MCP supporting either OAuth or API-key authentication.",
    "description": "Honeycomb is an observability platform for exploring telemetry from distributed systems and applications. It helps teams investigate performance, reliability, and behavior using high-cardinality event, trace, and related operational data.",
    "credentials": {
      "hc_api_key": {
        "type": "compound",
        "label": "Honeycomb API key",
        "generateUrl": "https://ui.honeycomb.io/",
        "setup": "In Honeycomb, go to **Account** → **Team Settings** → **API Keys** to create or manage API keys. Honeycomb issues three key types documented at [Authentication](https://docs.honeycomb.io/api/authentication): **Ingest Keys**, **Configuration Keys**, and **Management Keys**. For REST API use, send either an Ingest/Configuration key in `X-Honeycomb-Team`, or a Management Key as `Authorization: Bearer <key ID>:<secret>`, depending on endpoint permissions. For MCP API-key auth, the troubleshooting guide says to use the API key in the form `<Key ID>:<Secret Key>` and some clients may pass that directly as the `Authorization` header. Store the secret at creation time; Honeycomb only returns some secrets once.",
        "acquisition": "manual"
      },
      "hc_mcp_oauth": {
        "type": "oauth2",
        "label": "Honeycomb MCP OAuth connection",
        "generateUrl": "https://docs.honeycomb.io/integrations/mcp/configuration-guide",
        "setup": "Use an MCP host with built-in OAuth support and add the Honeycomb MCP server from [Connecting AI Agents to Honeycomb MCP](https://docs.honeycomb.io/integrations/mcp/configuration-guide). Honeycomb recommends OAuth for interactive agents. For example, add the remote MCP endpoint `https://mcp.honeycomb.io/mcp` (or EU `https://mcp.eu1.honeycomb.io/mcp`) in a compatible host such as Cursor, VS Code, Claude, Claude Code, or Amazon Q Developer, then complete the sign-in flow when prompted.",
        "acquisition": "manual"
